    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1670"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1670">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11 D 29.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 4, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>To-day at Cocoa Grove one American civilian killed, three wounded, and seven
                    infantry privates, two marine privates wounded, by Panaman police. Three
                    policemen wounded, one reported killed. Investigation thus far indicates an
                    attack by armed police on unarmed soldiers, for no cause except some altercation
                    among themselves.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
